Parliament, Wednesday, 28 August 2019 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow hold a media briefing on its oversight visits to the Kusile and Medupi power stations. Details of the media briefing are as follows: Date : Thursday, 29 August 2019
	Time : 13:00
	Venue : Jupiter Room, Eskom Conference Centre, Megawatt Park, Sunninghill ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR MKHULEKO HLENGWA. For media enquiries, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8062
	Cell: 081 377 0686
	Email: fndenze@parliament.gov.za The President is not a member of Parliament. After an MP is elected as President, he or she loses the seat and the vacancy is filled by the next eligible person from the same party.Read more